Peter Dada, Akure Some suspected hoodlums allegedly attacked Isinigbo Community in Akure North Local Government Area of Ondo State on Friday morning, destroying properties. It was gathered that the attack was not unconnected with the communal crisis between the Isinigbo Community and a neighbouring community of Ode which had earlier been attacked also a few days ago. A source said two unidentified persons were killed in the attack while many houses were burnt down, including the palace of the traditional ruler of the community by the suspected hoodlums. The state Police Public Relations Officer, Mr Tee-Leo Ikoro, confirmed the incident to The PUNCH. Details laterâ€¦